Matplotlib\
CSV\
Math\
Statistics\
Pandas\
Numpy\
Scipy.stats \
Scipy.Optimize\
Itertools\
SKlearn.metrics\
Sqrt\
Rpy2\
Re\
Os\
GLOB\
Randomcolor \
\
TO INPUT A SINGLE FILE, PUT INTO THE TERMINAL:\
\
\

\f1\b0 python combined_scripts.py --input_file <raw data file> \

\f0\b \
TO INPUT A PATH, PUT INTO THE TERMINAL:\
\
\

\f1\b0 python combined_scripts.py --input_path <folder path> 
\f0\b \
\
TO INPUT A PATH, PUT INTO THE TERMINAL:\
\
\

\f1\b0 python combined_scripts.py --combination_drugs drug_1 drug_2 drug_3  --input_file <raw data file>\
\
^^^ Make sure there is space between the drug names; it is not separated by commas.\
\

\f0\b If you have multiple graphs with multiple drug combinations, simply go: 
\f1\b0 \
\
python combined_scripts.py --combination_drugs drug_1 drug_2 drug_3 --combination_drugs drug_6 drug_5 \'97input_file_combination <raw data file>\
\

\f0\b \ul OUTPUTS\

\f1\b0 \ulnone You will get a PDF/PDFs of your graph(s). \
You will also get a textfile containing your IC50s and Scatter Index value for each drug.\
Some files may be created, and then deleted after the script is done running. That is part of the script; it is used to prevent clutter buildup. 
